<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880419-0177 </DOCNO><HL> Horizon Industries Places Notes </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HRZN </CO><DATELINE> CALHOUN, Ga.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Horizon Industries Inc. said it raised $25 million in a private placement of senior unsecured notes with insurance companies.    &quot;This financing significantly reduces our short-term bank borrowings and provides permanent financing for the major capital expansion programs completed in 1987,&quot; said Peter R. Spirer, chairman of the carpet maker.    Annual interest on the 10-year debt is 9.5%, with $1,250,000 of principal repayable at the end of each of the first five years and $3,750,000 repayable annually thereafter, Horizon said. </TEXT></DOC>